880 FRONT STREET, ROOM 6293
SAN DIEGO, CA 92101-8893
DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE
NOTICE OF LIEN FOR FINE, RESTITIUTION,
AND/OR SPECIAL ASSESSMENT IMPOSED
PURSUANT TO THE ANTI-TERRORISM AND
EFFECTIVE DEATH PENALTY ACT OF 1996
United States Attomey's Office for
Serial Number
the Southern District of California
2014A75465/001
Notice is hereby given of a lien against the property of the defendant named below. Pursuant to Title 18, United States
Code, $ 3613(c), a fine imposed pursuant to the provisions of subchapter C of chapter 227 or an order of restitution imposed pursuant
to enumerated sections of this title, is a lien in favor of the United States upon all property belonging to the person fined or ordered
to pay restitution. Pursuant to Title 18, United States Code, $ 3013(b), special assessments shall be collected in the same manner
as fines and also serve as a lien in favor of the United States. Pursuant to $ 3613(d), a notice of lien shall be considered a notice of
lien for taxes to the United States for the purpose of any State or local law providing for the filing of a notice of a tax lien. The lien
arises at the time of the entry of judgment and continues until the liability is satisfied, remitted, set aside, or becomes unenforceable
pursuant to $ 3613(b) for fines and restitution, and $ 3013(c) for special assessments.
Name of Defendant/SSN: Paul Joyce/++ *-**- 2571
Unofficial Copy
Residence: 1752 NW Market Street, Seattle, WA 98107
Current Balance of Judgment: $117,684.72
Court Imposing Judgment: United States District Court for the Southern District of California
Court Number: 14CR2543-JLS
Date of Entry of Judgment: January 30, 2015
Rate of Interest: 0.21%
The defendant shall pay interest on any fine or restitution at the rate stated above pursuant to 18 U.S.C. $ 3612(f). If payment
becomes past due, penalties in an amount equal to 10 percent of the delinquent principal amount shall be due. If payment is in
default, an additional amount equal to 15 percent of the principal amount in default shall be due. 18 U.S.C. $ 3612(g).
IMPORTANT EXPIRATION INFORMATION-With respect to the lien listed above, this notice shall remain in effect pursuant
to the provisions of 18 U.S.C. $ 3613 for fines and restitution, and 18 U.S.C. $ 3013(c) for special assessments.
Place of Filing: King County Recorder's Office, King County Admn ., Bldg ., 500 Fourth Avenue, Ste. 430, Seattle, WA 98104.
This notice was prepared and signed at United States Attorney's Office, 880 Front Street, Room 6293, San Diego, CA 92101-8893
on April 6, 2022.
Signature
michael F. Kaplan
MICHAEL F. KAPLAN
(619) 546-9488
Title
